UNITED STATES of America, Plaintiff-Appellee, v. El Luterio OROZCO-PINEDA, a.k.a. Luterio, a.k.a. Lute, Defendant-Appellant. No. 09-12393

Non-Argument Calendar.

United States Court of Appeals, Eleventh Circuit. Dec. 4, 2009. Jeffrey Davis, John Andrew Horn, U.S. Attorney’s Office, Atlanta, GA, for Plaintiff-Appellee. Michael H. Saul, Marietta, GA, for Defendant-Appellant. Before CARNES, MARCUS and KRAVITCH, Circuit Judges. PER CURIAM:

Michael H. Saul, appointed counsel for El Luterio Orozco-Pineda in this direct criminal appeal, has moved to withdraw from further representation of the appellant and filed a brief pursuant to Anders v. California, 386 U.S. 738, 87 S.Ct. 1396, 18 L.Ed.2d 493 (1967). Because independent examination of the entire record reveals no arguable issues of merit, counsel’s motion to withdraw is GRANTED, and Orozco’s conviction and sentence are AFFIRMED.
